                            <comment id="16025569" author="vahid" created="Thu, 25 May 2017 23:49:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ewencp&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ewencp&quot;&gt;ewencp&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ll work on a KIP for changing the required permission for offset fetch. I am wondering why the required permission for heartbeat is set to Read (vs. Describe). Because it seems that heartbeat is non-mutating by itself and during the processing of a heartbeat request no change occurs to the group or the consumer. Also, cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hachikuji&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hachikuji&quot;&gt;hachikuji&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16025746" author="ewencp" created="Fri, 26 May 2017 03:24:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vahid&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vahid&quot;&gt;vahid&lt;/a&gt; Honestly not sure &amp;#8211; there are a number of permissions that I find odd choices, especially in the consumer. Unfortunately I didn&apos;t participate in the discussions/patches that introduced those, so I&apos;m not sure of the reasoning. I&apos;ve discussed this previously with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hachikuji&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hachikuji&quot;&gt;hachikuji&lt;/a&gt; and iirc he also agreed some of them may seem a bit odd. Not sure if he has anything more to add here wrt your specific question though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
